# Nawy Mini API — sample requests
# Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension (or JetBrains HTTP client).
# Click "Send Request" above each block.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
# For the Docker stack instead, use: http://localhost:3101

### List apartments (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/apartments?page=1&limit=9

### Search apartments (by unit name / number / project)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/apartments/search?search=garden

### Get a single apartment (replace the id with a real one)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/apartments/REPLACE_WITH_APARTMENT_ID

### Log in -> returns a JWT (valid 1 hour)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "Admin@nawy.com",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}

### Create an apartment (uses the token from the login request above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/apartments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "unitName": "Sample Unit",
  "unitNumber": "SAMPLE-001",
  "project": "Sample Project",
  "description": "Created from the .http file.",
  "price": 5000000,
  "bedrooms": 2,
  "bathrooms": 1,
  "area": 120
}
